pr_body:
**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**
pygeoapi as of now implements [OGC API - Features - Part 1: Core](http://docs.opengeospatial.org/is/17-069r3/17-069r3.html) in which the only HTTP verb supported is GET. So users can perform only read operations from the data providers through the RESTful interface of pygeoapi. This won't cover the needs of most users as they would expect a complete RESTful interface which provides all of the CRUD operations on data providers.

**Describe the solution you'd like**
[OGC API - Features - Part 4: Simple Transactions](http://docs.opengeospatial.org/DRAFTS/20-002.html) has defined schemas for creation, updating, replacement, and deletion of resource items via POST, PATCH, PUT, and DELETE HTTP verbs. By implementing this in pygeoapi, we can get a complete RESTful interface which provides all of the CRUD operations on data providers.

**Describe alternatives you've considered**
None

**Additional context**
I have proposed a sample openapi document with endpoints supporting POST, PATCH, PUT, and DELETE verbs. I have also added a new transaction flag to the config file which tells whether a particular collection resource supports data transactions or not. The generate-openapi-document command now generates transaction schemas in the openapi document if the transactions flag is set to true for the corresponding resource in the config file. I have also added test cases for transaction support for collections and for checking whether generated schemas of all four data transaction operations are in compliance with the proposed schemas. I have also added a subsection for transactions under configuration in RTD. The code passed flake8 linting and unit tests. The build for the data-transaction-GSoC-1 branch was successful in Travis.

- pygeoapi configuration with transactions flag
```
resources:
    obs:
        type: collection
        extensions:
             transactions: True
```

- Generated OpenAPI JSON document
![Screen Shot 2020-07-03 at 10 42 30 PM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35272003/86488569-0f18c800-bd7f-11ea-9fb2-173615a762df.png)

- Passing test cases
![Screen Shot 2020-07-03 at 10 42 06 PM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35272003/86488521-ded12980-bd7e-11ea-9ad9-117135e3fdf7.png)

- Travis Build
https://travis-ci.org/github/alex-mathew/pygeoapi/builds/704651775
![Screen Shot 2020-07-03 at 11 07 00 PM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35272003/86489447-02e23a00-bd82-11ea-9bf0-cdafb479dde9.png)

- RTD
https://pygeoapi-data-transaction.readthedocs.io/en/data-transaction-gsoc-1/configuration.html#data-transactions
![Screen Shot 2020-07-08 at 11 37 39 PM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35272003/86954739-263b2980-c174-11ea-9021-67f1d1e3d38e.png)

pr_body:
**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**
pygeoapi as of now implements [OGC API - Features - Part 1: Core](http://docs.opengeospatial.org/is/17-069r3/17-069r3.html) in which the only HTTP verb supported is GET. So users can perform only read operations from the data providers through the RESTful interface of pygeoapi. This won't cover the needs of most users as they would expect a complete RESTful interface which provides all of the CRUD operations on data providers.

**Describe the solution you'd like**
[OGC API - Features - Part 4: Simple Transactions](http://docs.opengeospatial.org/DRAFTS/20-002.html) has defined schemas for creation, updating, replacement, and deletion of resource items via POST, PATCH, PUT, and DELETE HTTP verbs. By implementing this in pygeoapi, we can get a complete RESTful interface which provides all of the CRUD operations on data providers.

**Describe alternatives you've considered**
None

**Additional context**
This PR is a continuation of #483 (Data Transaction GSoC Phase 1) which consisted of openapidoc proposal and generation for simple transaction support. In this PR, I have implemented the proposal from #483 for geojson and csv providers.

-  Enabling transactions in pygeoapi configuration
```
resources:
    obs:
        type: collection
        providers:
            - type: feature
              extensions:
                    - type: transaction
                      enabled: true
```

pr_body:
**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**
pygeoapi as of now implements [OGC API - Features - Part 1: Core](http://docs.opengeospatial.org/is/17-069r3/17-069r3.html) in which the only HTTP verb supported is GET. So users can perform only read operations from the data providers through the RESTful interface of pygeoapi. This won't cover the needs of most users as they would expect a complete RESTful interface which provides all of the CRUD operations on data providers.

**Describe the solution you'd like**
[OGC API - Features - Part 4: Simple Transactions](http://docs.opengeospatial.org/DRAFTS/20-002.html) has defined schemas for creation, updating, replacement, and deletion of resource items via POST, PATCH, PUT, and DELETE HTTP verbs. By implementing this in pygeoapi, we can get a complete RESTful interface which provides all of the CRUD operations on data providers.

**Describe alternatives you've considered**
None

**Additional context**
This PR is a continuation of #518 (Data Transaction GSoC Phase 2) which consisted of transaction implementation in GeoJSON and CSV providers. In this PR, I have implemented the proposal from #508 for Postgres and SQLite providers. Most of the implementation has been done but the SQLite POST even though is running fine, seem to convert the geojson geometry to None.
